{"id":14881538,"mediaExerciseId":"2163dd2f-6b96-43d7-8cb8-be8ea1c37377","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"16","chapterTitle":"Financial Leverage and Capital Structure Policy","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"16.7","sectionTitle":"The Pie Again","pageNumber":558,"solutions":[{"id":5992164,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"$a)$ \nSo the firm must pay the shareholders a return on their investment, shareholders have a claim to the company's cash flow.\n\nBondholders must be paid interest regularly, and the principal must be repaid when the bonds mature, as a consequence, they have a claim on the company's cash flow.\n\nA government supplies the corporation with a variety of services, for the usage of these facilities, a company must pay recurring taxes to the government, such taxes are treated as a claim on the company's cash flow, various parties who provide services to the company have a claim on the company's cash flow inside the case of bankruptcy and tax fees.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":369,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/a4290c5078f9a27dead2c5f7d51ec109/lateximg_large.png","width":1026},"regular":{"height":185,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/a4290c5078f9a27dead2c5f7d51ec109/lateximg.png","width":513}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"$b)$ The marketed claims are those which can be purchased and sold on financial markets, while non-marketed claims are those which can be bought and sold at financial markets.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/8d49aef50a12002f354e539f49c46e02/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/8d49aef50a12002f354e539f49c46e02/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$c)$ The overall worth of all rights to a firm's cash flows remains constant at all degrees of financial leverage, according to the expanded pie model, however, the relative prices of such claims change as the level of financial leverage varies.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/e54cd46f3fcc00d0c39342ffcd2ae332/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2d2958992b39aa51f8f295c2bff69aeb/e54cd46f3fcc00d0c39342ffcd2ae332/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"6899cbfb-41ab-4b48-bb27-c84e5c6cef54","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881539,"exerciseName":"8","page":560,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4bb09f0b-5ada-4c8e-922e-3f7086cc2c19","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-16-exercises-8-4bb09f0b-5ada-4c8e-922e-3f7086cc2c19"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881537,"exerciseName":"6","page":556,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9d43e5a0-7c5b-4967-aec5-243934d91125","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-16-exercises-6-9d43e5a0-7c5b-4967-aec5-243934d91125"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-16-exercises-7-2163dd2f-6b96-43d7-8cb8-be8ea1c37377"}